🌐 🔥 COMPLETE DNS + DOMAIN SETUP (PRODUCTION)

We will handle:

Public DNS (for users)
Private DNS (for Azure internal resolution)
🧭 🥇 PART 1: PUBLIC DNS (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 This is what makes your site accessible:

✅ Step 1: Get App Gateway Public IP
Go to:
Application Gateway → Frontend IP
Copy Public IP
✅ Step 2: Go to Domain Provider

Example:

GoDaddy / Namecheap / Azure DNS
✅ Step 3: Create DNS Record
Option A: Root Domain
Type: A Record
Name: @
Value: <App Gateway Public IP>
Option B: Subdomain (Recommended)
Type: A Record
Name: www
Value: <App Gateway Public IP>
✅ Step 4: Verify

After 5–10 mins:

nslookup www.xyz.com

✔ Should resolve to App Gateway IP

🌐 🔥 PART 2: CUSTOM DOMAIN IN APP SERVICE

Even though traffic goes via App Gateway, you still map domain.

Step:

👉 App Service → Custom Domains → Add

Domain: www.xyz.com
Validate ownership
🔐 🔥 PART 3: PRIVATE DNS (CRITICAL FOR PRIVATE ENDPOINTS)

👉 Without this, your app will NOT connect to SQL ❌

✅ Step 1: Create Private DNS Zones

Go to:
👉 Private DNS Zones → Create

Create these:

Service	DNS Zone
SQL	privatelink.database.windows.net
App Service	privatelink.azurewebsites.net
✅ Step 2: Link to VNet

For each DNS zone:

Go to Virtual Network Links
Link:
vnet-xyz-prod-ci
✅ Step 3: Auto Registration

✔ Enable while creating Private Endpoint

✅ Step 4: Verify DNS Resolution

From VM:

nslookup sql-xyz-prod-ci.database.windows.net

✔ Should return Private IP (10.x.x.x)

🔥 WHY THIS IS IMPORTANT

Without Private DNS:

App → SQL (Public IP) ❌

With Private DNS:

App → SQL (Private IP) ✅
🔐 🔥 PART 4: SSL (PFX FROM APP TEAM)

Since you said:

👉 “PFX will be given by app team”

We simplify:

✅ Option 1: Upload Directly to App Gateway

👉 Application Gateway → Listener → HTTPS

Upload PFX
Enter password
✅ Option 2 (Better): Store in Key Vault

Even if given by app team:

Upload to Key Vault
Reference in App Gateway

👉 More secure & reusable

🧠 FINAL DNS FLOW
User → www.xyz.com
       ↓
Public DNS → App Gateway Public IP
       ↓
App Gateway
       ↓
App Service (via private routing)
       ↓
Private DNS
       ↓
SQL Private Endpoint
🎯 FINAL CHECKLIST (DON’T MISS)

✔ Public DNS → App Gateway
✔ Custom Domain → App Service
✔ Private DNS → SQL + App
✔ VNet linked to DNS
✔ nslookup returns private IP

